stylometry:
Price and demand are related. When price increases, demand decreases and vice versa. This is call price elasticity of demand. The tradeoff between price and demand is that we want to set a price high enough to cover our costs, but not too high where our demand will drop to a point where we will not sell enough of the product to cover the costs anyways. The best possible way to decide is to look at the industy competitors. Try to set a price in comparison to competitors in relation to the quality of the product. If our product is believe to be better than the competitors set a slightly higher price. If it is lower quality, then set a slightly lower price.
We could use a model by setting up chart showing the elasticity of demand curve and its relation to the amount of profits we will receive due to the price we set.
